History: Chronic congestive heart failure and increasing cough.
Findings: PA and lateral upright chest radiographs were reviewed in comparison to. Cardiomegaly is unchanged, moderate. The mediastinum is stable. There is interval improvement of interstitial pulmonary edema. Bilateral pleural effusions are unchanged with associated areas of atelectasis, but no new consolidation is seen. Compression fractures are seen along the spinal column with two areas of vertebroplasty.
